        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(proxy): apply enhanced NO_PROXY matching to global undici dispatcher (fixes #95998)",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes #95998.\n\nWhen `HTTPS_PROXY` is set, the global EnvHttpProxyAgent routes ALL requests through the proxy — including internal plugin requests that should bypass via `NO_PROXY`. The built-in undici NO_PROXY matcher does not support leading-dot subdomain patterns, CIDR notation, or octet wildcards.\n\nOpenClaw already has `matchesNoProxy()` that handles these — but it was only used by provider helpers, not the global dispatcher.\n\n## Changes Made\n\n1. **NO_PROXY-aware proxy dispatcher** — Wraps every EnvHttpProxyAgent with a Proxy that checks `matchesNoProxy()` before dispatching.\n\n2. **Lifecycle synchronization (P1 fix)** — Promise-style `close()`/`destroy()` now await both the bypass agent AND the proxy dispatcher. `destroy(err)` arguments are forwarded correctly.\n\n3. **no_proxy precedence (P1 fix)** — Empty lowercase `no_proxy` now correctly shadows uppercase `NO_PROXY`, matching undici's EnvHttpProxyAgent semantics.\n\n4. **Timeout/connect consistency** — `forceResetGlobalDispatcher` passes `connect` options to the bypass agent.\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Unit tests (90/90 passed):**\n```\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/infra/net/proxy-env.test.ts\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  55 passed (55)\n\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/infra/net/undici-global-dispatcher.test.ts\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  35 passed (35)\n```\n\n**no_proxy precedence (matching undici semantics):**\n```\n  ✅ empty no_proxy shadows NO_PROXY: false (correct — bypass nothing)\n  ✅ only NO_PROXY (uppercase): true (fallback works)\n  ✅ no_proxy match: true (lowercase works)\n  ✅ non-matching: false\n```\n\n**CIDR and octet-wildcard support (undici built-in lacks these):**\n```\n  ✅ CIDR: 100.64.0.0/10 match\n  ✅ CIDR: 169.254.0.0/16 match\n  ✅ Octet wildcard: 100.100.*.*\n  ✅ Subdomain: .myqcloud.com\n```\n\n## AI Assistance\n\n- AI-assisted: Yes",
